/bin/zsh -lc "sed -n '220,420p' ../codex_findings.md" in /Users/lu/Desktop/Red_V1G/2025-05-dodo-cross-chain-dex/omni-chain-contracts/contracts succeeded in 52ms:
- `GatewaySend`

Affected lines:
- `contracts/GatewaySend.sol:195`
- `contracts/GatewaySend.sol:202`
- `contracts/GatewaySend.sol:341`
- `contracts/GatewaySend.sol:358`
- `contracts/GatewaySend.sol:366`

Description:
On the destination side, `GatewaySend.onCall()` trusts the payload-defined `amount` and `params.fromTokenAmount` instead of binding them to the real inbound asset/value.

For ERC20 flows, an inflated `params.fromTokenAmount` can make DODO consume residual same-token inventory.  
For ETH same-token flows, the function can pay out the payload-defined `amount` instead of actual `msg.value`, consuming any ETH already sitting in the contract.

Impact:
Residual balances in `GatewaySend` can be drained through crafted destination-side payloads.

Recommendation:
Bind decoded amount fields to the actual inbound amount/value before any approval, swap, or payout.
