with swap output token different from `asset`.","Obtain nonzero `outputAmount` or force it via crafted swap data.","The contract deposits `outputAmount` of the attacker-chosen `asset` to the gateway, consuming contract reserves."],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-011","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Refund key collisions and zero-key handling can overwrite entries, block recording, or lock refunds","locations":["GatewayTransferNative.sol:628","GatewayTransferNative.sol:648","GatewayTransferNative.sol:661","GatewayTransferNative.sol:670","GatewayTransferNative.sol:683","GatewayCrossChain.sol:561","GatewayCrossChain.sol:585"],"claim":"Refunds are keyed only by `externalId`. `GatewayTransferNative` overwrites `refundInfos[externalId]` without existence checks, and `claimRefund` rejects entries with zero-valued `externalId`, making key `0x0` refunds unclaimable. `GatewayCrossChain` uses a zero-sentinel duplicate guard that can be bypassed for `externalId == 0x0`, while non-zero collisions revert with `REFUND_INFO_ALREADY_EXISTS` and block later recording.","impact":"Attackers can cause refund misdirection or overwrite, prevent later callback refund recording for colliding non-zero keys, and permanently lock refunds stored under `externalId == 0x0`.","paths":["Trigger a callback path that stores `refundInfos[externalId]` for key `X` in `GatewayTransferNative`; a later callback with the same key overwrites previous refund metadata.","Pre-populate `GatewayCrossChain.refundInfos[X]` for non-zero `X`; subsequent callbacks for the same key revert on the duplicate guard and fail to record the new refund.","Supply or propagate `externalId == 0x0` so callbacks store under key zero; `GatewayTransferNative.claimRefund(0x0)` always reverts due to the sentinel check."],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-012","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"AccountEncoder.decompressAccounts builds invalid memory layout for `Ac