ount, address asset, ...)`, ERC20 intake checks only `transferFrom` boolean success and never reconciles actual balance delta before approving and depositing the full nominal `amount` to the gateway.","impact":"With fee-on-transfer or deflationary ERC20s, the contract may receive less than `amount` but still bridge `amount`; any deficit is covered from pre-existing contract balances, enabling reserve drain and insolvency over repeated calls.","paths":["Call `depositAndCall(targetContract, amount, asset, ...)` using a taxed ERC20.","The contract receives less than `amount` but still approves and deposits full `amount` to the gateway.","The gateway pull succeeds using contract-held inventory to cover the shortfall, transferring value to an attacker-controlled cross-chain flow."],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-017","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"GatewaySend revert handler lacks native-asset refund path and can strand reverted ETH","locations":["GatewaySend.sol:393","GatewaySend.sol:396"],"claim":"`onRevert` always calls ERC20-style `TransferHelper.safeTransfer(context.asset, ...)` and has no branch for native refunds. For gas-token reverts where `context.asset` is empty or zero-address, this call does not transfer ETH back to the user.","impact":"Failed ETH-origin cross-chain calls can be finalized without refunding the sender, leaving reverted value stranded in `GatewaySend` and exposed to secondary reserve-drain bugs.","paths":["A user submits an ETH `depositAndCall` through `GatewaySend`.","Destination execution fails and the gateway triggers `onRevert` with gas-token context.","The handler attempts token transfer using `context.asset` instead of native ETH transfer, so the sender is not refunded."],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-018","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Swap output asset is not bound to target payout token before withdrawal/transfer","locations":["GatewayCrossChain.sol:376","GatewayCrossChain.sol:492","GatewayCrossChain.sol:432","GatewayTransferNative.sol:414","GatewayTransferNative.sol:422","GatewayTransferNative.sol:456","GatewayTransferNative.sol:541","GatewayTransferNative.sol:574"],"claim":"Both contracts execute DODO swaps using `params.toToken` but later withdraw or transfer `decoded.targetZRC20` without enforcing `params.toToken == decoded.targetZRC20`, or otherwise proving that the swapped asset matches the payout asset.","impact":"Attackers can route swaps into a different or cheap token while forcing payout or withdrawal in a valuable reserve token, draining contract-held inventories.","paths":["Craft swap payload where `params.toToken` is not `decoded.targetZRC20` and yields a controllable `outputAmount`.","Trigger `GatewayCrossChain.onCall`, `GatewayTransferNative.withdrawToNativeChain`, or `GatewayTransferNative.onCall` swap branches.","The contract treats numeric `outputAmount` as an amount of `decoded.targetZRC20` and transfers or withdraws that token from reserves."],"round":4,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-022","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"`amountInMax`-based post-swap check can cause avoidable withdrawal reverts","locations":["GatewayTransferNative.sol:338","GatewayTransferNative.sol:352","GatewayTransferNative.sol:357"],"claim":"`_swapAndSendERC20Tokens` computes `amountInMax` with slippage buffer, executes the swap, but then checks `targetAmount - amountInMax > 0` instead of `targetAmount - amounts[0] > 0`. This can revert even when actual spent input leaves a positive withdrawable remainder.","impact":"Valid withdrawal flows can fail unnecessarily, causing cross-chain execution failures or refunds and enabling practical route-level liveness degradation when quotes are pushed near the threshold.","paths":["Increase quote pressure, or rely on high configured slippage, so `amountInMax >= targetAmount` while actual `amounts[0] < targetAmount`.","`swapTokensForExactTokens` succeeds, but the subsequent `require(targetAmount - amountInMax > 0)` reverts.","The user-facing withdrawal path fails despite sufficient actual post-swap balance."],"round":4,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-023","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Exact-output Uniswap approval pattern can DoS strict-approve tokens","locations":["GatewayCrossChain.sol:342","GatewayCrossChain.sol:343","GatewayCrossChain.sol:347","GatewayTransferNative.sol:338","GatewayTransferNative.sol:339","GatewayTransferNative.sol:343"],"claim":"Both contracts approve `amountInMax` before `swapTokensForExactTokens`. Because exact-output swaps commonly spend less than `amountInMax`, leftover router allowance remains. Later calls set another non-zero allowance without zero-reset.","impact":"For tokens that enforce zero-first allowance updates, future swaps on affected routes revert, causing persistent token-pair liveness failure until allowance is manually cleared.","paths":["Run an exact-output gas-fee swap where `amounts[0] < amountInMax`.","Residual allowance to `UniswapRouter` remains non-zero.","A subsequent call executes `approve(UniswapRouter, newAmountInMax)` from non-zero allowance and strict token logic reverts."],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-024","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"GatewaySend ETH input flows ignore `amount` and consume full `msg.value`","locations":["GatewaySend.sol:202","GatewaySend.sol:233","GatewaySend.sol:245","GatewaySend.sol:308","GatewaySend.sol:311"],"claim":"Both ETH-input `depositAndCall` paths only require `msg.value >= amount`, but downstream consume the full `msg.value`: the direct overload deposits `msg.value` to the gateway, and the swap overload forwards `msg.value` into DODO instead of binding ETH spend to `amount`.","impact":"Callers and integrators can unintentionally spend or bridge more ETH than intended, causing direct user loss and accounting mismatches.","paths":["Invoke the direct ETH overload with `msg.value > amount`; the function deposits full `msg.value` to the gateway even though the API parameter indicates a smaller amount.","Invoke the swap ETH overload with `fromToken == _ETH_ADDRESS_` and `msg.value > amount`; `_doMixSwap` forwards full `msg.value` to DODO with no contract-side cap or refund of excess."],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_reviewer"]},{"id":"F-025","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"GatewayTransferNative refund-claimed event emits zero token/amount due to storage read after delete","locations":["GatewayTransferNative.sol:692","GatewayTransferNative.sol:694","GatewayTransferNative.sol:696","GatewayTransferNative.sol:697"],"claim":"`claimRefund` stores `refundInfo` as a storage pointer, deletes `refundInfos[externalId]`, then emits `EddyCrossChainRefundClaimed` using `refundInfo.token` and `refundInfo.amount` from the deleted slot.","impact":"Off-chain accounting, monitoring, and incident response that rely on the claim event can record zeroed token or amount values, weakening operational controls and reconciliation.","paths":["Execute any successful `claimRefund(externalId)` in `GatewayTransferNative`.","The function transfers funds, deletes the mapping entry, and then reads fields via the stale storage reference for the event.","The event logs zero token or amount despite a real payout."],"round":8,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-026","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"GatewaySend `onCall` return type is ABI-incompatible with ZetaChain `Callable`","locations":["GatewaySend.sol:344","GatewaySend.sol:385","node_modules/@zetachain/protocol-contracts/contracts/evm/interfaces/IGatewayEVM.sol:229","node_modules/@zetachain/protocol-contracts/contracts/evm/GatewayEVM.sol:439"],"claim":"`GatewaySend.onCall` is declared `returns (bytes4)` and returns `\"\"`, but `IGatewayEVM.Callable.onCall` requires `returns (bytes memory)`. `GatewayEVM` invokes authenticated deliveries via `Callable(destination).onCall(...)`, so the caller ABI-decodes returndata as dynamic bytes and reverts on the fixed-size `bytes4` return payload.","impact":"Authenticated cross-chain deliveries targeting `GatewaySend` cannot complete; the gateway call reverts and the destination settlement path is effectively bricked, forcing failure or refund handling for every attempted delivery.","paths":["A user targets `GatewaySend` as the destination contract for an authenticated cross-chain call.","`GatewayEVM` performs `Callable(destination).onCall(...)` and expects a dynamic `bytes` return.","`GatewaySend.onCall` returns fixed-size `bytes4`; ABI decoding in the gateway reverts, rolling back the entire destination execution."],"round":9,"source_agents":["merge_reviewer"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"GatewayTransferNative local-delivery swaps spend the pre-fee amount and can siphon reserves","source_agents":["codex_1"],"reason":"Merged into existing F-001; this is the already-accepted pre-fee branch of the broader attacker-controlled swap-parameter reserve-drain issue."},{"title":"GatewaySend destination settlement trusts nominal ERC20 pull amounts and can spend reserves on taxed or soft-failing tokens","source_agents":["codex_1"],"reason":"Not kept separately because authenticated `GatewaySend.onCall` execution is presently bricked by F-026, so this destination-side settlement path is unreachable in the current integration."},{"title":"Cross-chain withdrawal logic never binds `dstChainId` to `targetZRC20` and can route funds through the wrong chain-specific path","source_agents":["codex_1"],"reason":"Rejected as a user-controlled misconfiguration issue; the actual destination route is determined by `targetZRC20`, and the code support here is insufficient for a cross-user exploit, reserve drain, or permissionless protocol-level DoS."},{"title":"Native-input `withdrawToNativeChain` lets callers bypass platform fees by decoupling `amount` from `msg.value`","source_agents":["codex_1"],"reason":"Merged into F-004; it is another consequence of the same nominal-amount-versus-actual-funding bug in `withdrawToNativeChain`."},{"title":"GatewaySend depositAndCall does not verify swap output or return funds on swap failure","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Rejected; swap failure reverts the whole transaction, and low output is governed by user-supplied DODO parameters rather than a distinct protocol bug."},{"title":"GatewaySend onCall uses message amount instead of actual token balance","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Not kept separately because authenticated `GatewaySend.onCall` execution is presently bricked by F-026, so this destination-side path is unreachable in the current integration."},{"title":"GatewayTransferNative.claimRefund reads storage after delete allowing double-claim with reentrancy","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Rejected as an inaccurate conflation of two existing issues: reentrancy before delete is already F-006, while post-delete storage reads only affect event data and are already F-025."},{"title":"Platform fee calculation ignores token decimals causing severe undercharging","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Rejected; fee calculation on raw token units is standard and does not inherently mis-handle decimals."},{"title":"Public withdraw function in GatewayTransferNative lacks access control and can be abused","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Merged into existing F-008; this is the same public-withdraw-plus-residual-allowance issue already captured."},{"title":"No deadline check in Uniswap swap allowing stale trades","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Rejected; the code passes `block.timestamp + MAX_DEADLINE` at execution time, so this is not a separate stale-deadline bug."},{"title":"onRevert uses .transfer for ETH which can DoS smart contract receivers","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Rejected as incorrect; the relevant bug is the missing native-refund branch already captured by F-017, not use of Solidity